article.headline: High Point 72, Limestone 43
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. -- Eugene Harris scored 17 points to lead High Point to a 72-43 victory over Limestone College on Wednesday night. Harris shot 6 of 13 from the field, including four 3-pointers. David Campbell also chipped in for the Panthers (4-5) with 12 points, six rebounds and six assists. Limestone (2-5) was led by Michael Barrett, who scored 19 points. The Panthers shot 47.5 percent from the field (28-for-59), while Limestone managed to shoot only 29.6 percent (16-for-54). High Point also outrebounded Limestone 46-26. After starting the season with a 2-0 record, the Saints have lost five straight games.
